{
  "stem": "802.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I don't know if I answered your question totally about the-- oh, yes, we studied Hebrew, my sister and I.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But we did not study the Ashkenazi, that is the-- the Hebrew for-- for prayer, but rather the modern Hebrew, which is essentially Sephardic.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So both my sister and I had four years of Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We had a tutor who came home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But I must confess, I really don't understand much, but I can read.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And rather interestingly, when I was writing my book, never really learned to read Yiddish, I was able to use the Hebrew alphabet, because the Yiddish language has a Hebrew alphabet.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I was able to read the Yiddish poetry.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And since I speak Yiddish and I understand it very well, and I speak it very well, I-- you know, that-- that having learned Hebrew was extremely useful in my translating the poetry.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, they spoke Yiddish at home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they spoke Polish to us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were bilingual immediately, even though we did not speak much Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think the reason for it was the anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if one spoke with a Yiddish accent, it was rather dangerous.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they wanted us to speak as pure a Polish as we possibly could.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you know, these were stratagems people used [LAUGHS] to try to make life more tolerable, because the anti-Semitism, as I recall it, was universal.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Certainly, where we lived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Although, we lived in the Jewish quarters, but we constantly heard about-- especially just before the war, the beards shorn off the faces of Orthodox people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And as I said, there was a church across the street from us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And even before the war, for a short period-- I don't remember precisely when we moved, in '38, or '39.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
